# ===========================================================================
# DENY-BY-DEFAULT .gitignore  (safest policy for sensitive legal data)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# We ignore EVERYTHING first, then explicitly allow back only the source code
# and config *templates*. This guarantees that client contract files (PDFs,
# DOCX, TIFFs, .msg, etc.), the .env secret file, and generated output can
# NEVER be committed by accident — far safer than trying to blocklist every
# contract file type or client folder by name.
#
# >>> To track a NEW source file later, add another "!<filename>" line below. <<<
# ===========================================================================

# 1) Ignore everything — including:
#       - the "BLUE CROSS TEXAS FEDERAL CREDIT UNION/" contract folder
#         (and any other client/contract folder you drop in later)
#       - output/ and extraction_cache.json (generated artifacts)
#       - .env (your real API key)
#       - __pycache__/, *.pyc, virtual envs, IDE files, etc.
*

# 2) Allow back ONLY the tool's source + setup files (all live at the repo root).
!.gitignore
!.env.example
!requirements.txt
!VDI_SETUP.md
!contract_hierarchy_analyzer.py
!PC-PH-ProductNames_Dictionary_v2.xlsx

# NOTE: .env is intentionally NOT allowed back — it holds your real API key and
# must never leave your machine / the VDI. The contract folders and output/ are
# also intentionally excluded; place the contracts directly in the VDI instead.
